  "prompt": "If you open a microwave oven before the beep will it release deadly microwave radiation?",
  "response": "No, opening a microwave oven before it beeps does not release deadly microwave radiation. Microwave ovens are designed with safety mechanisms that prevent them from operating while the door is open. When you open the door, a switch is activated that stops the microwave from generating radiation. \n\nMicrowave radiation is only produced when the oven is securely closed and functioning properly. Therefore, it is safe to open the door at any time, including before it beeps, and no harmful radiation will be released. ",
